---
description: Never bypass git or hook safety. Invoke manually or by description when running git commands.
alwaysApply: false
---

Never propose or run any of the following without explicit user
authorization in the current session:

- `git push --force`, `git push -f`, `git push --force-with-lease`.
- `git push <remote> main` from a branch other than `main`/`master`.
- `git commit` while the current branch is `main` or `master`.
- `git reset --hard origin/main` or any destructive reset against
  upstream refs.
- `--no-verify`, `--no-gpg-sign`, or any flag that bypasses pre-commit
  or pre-push hooks.
- Rewriting committed history that has already been pushed.
- `rm -rf` against any path outside the current repo working tree.

**IF** a workflow appears to require any of the above, **STOP** and ask
the user. Git hooks in `.husky/` and agent hooks in `scripts/ai-hooks/`
(wired via `.claude/`, `.cursor/hooks.json`, `.codex/hooks.json`) will
refuse most of these — do not try to circumvent
them.
